cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.SE 

This paper is likely to belong to the "cs.NI" (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category as it discusses access control in Named Data Networking (NDN) architecture. It may also belong to the "cs.CR" (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it discusses encryption and decryption keys. Additionally, it may belong to the "cs.DC" (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category as it discusses how NDN's Interest-Data exchange can help NAC to function in case of intermittent connectivity. It may also belong to the "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks) sub-category as it discusses how NDN's hierarchically structured namespace allows NAC to support fine-grained access control policies. Finally, it may belong to the "cs.SE" (Software Engineering) sub-category as it discusses the design of the NAC scheme.
